      "id": "t25",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "CPM vs RPM — What's the Difference?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t26",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "CPM"
    },
    {
      "id": "t27",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "(Cost Per Mille) is what advertisers pay YouTube for every 1,000 ad impressions on your content. It's the gross rate — before YouTube takes its share."
    },
    {
      "id": "t28",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "RPM"
    },
    {
      "id": "t29",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "(Revenue Per Mille) is what you actually receive per 1,000 total video views — after YouTube's 45% cut and accounting for the fact that not every view serves an ad."
    },
    {
      "id": "t30",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "Key formula: RPM = CPM × 0.55 × monetization rate"
    },
    {
      "id": "t31",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Example: $10 CPM × 0.55 × 0.80 monetization ="
    },
    {
      "id": "t32",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "$4.40 RPM"
    },
    {
      "id": "t33",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Why Your Monetization Rate Matters"
    },
    {
      "id": "t34",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "Ad blockers reduce your effective monetization rate"
    },
    {
      "id": "t35",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "Viewers who skip ads immediately don't generate full revenue"
    },
    {
      "id": "t36",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "Non-monetized content (music, copyright claims) earns nothing"
    },
    {
      "id": "t37",
